        "created_at": "2026-01-12T16:45:49.122Z",
        "cooked": "<p>Hi</p>\n<p>Thanks for your reply.<br>\nIt is clear that ‚ÄúSignal uses the same PIN as MY phone‚Äôs lock screen‚Äù and I don‚Äôt really understand how this get to the point as in my post, it was not about the PIN code I posted about.</p>\n<p>I understand that ‚Äúthere wouldn‚Äôt be any added security‚Äù, but ‚ÄúUsing biometrics removes the need for something like this‚Äù is not a solution, mostly for (privacy and security driven) apps like Signal and shouldn‚Äôt be advised to users, I personally never used and will NOT use it, as it‚Äôs not as secure as PIN code, mostly in countries where low enforcers (or anyone else in case) can force you to unlock the screen with no straggle.</p>",
